@node OptionsH


## H ##


It removes the wave header of a file.
Is safer and faster for wave files than -F and also easier to use since you can
do it on several files at once.


                            @{" Back To The Options " link Options}  


@endnode
@node OptionsL


## L ##


It's a simple listing with diplaying the duration and the kbps.


                            @{" Back To The Options " link Options}  


@endnode
@node Optionsm


## m ##


It's the same as @{" M " link OptionsM1} but nothing is prompted on the screen.


                            @{" Back To The Options " link Options}  


@endnode
@node OptionsM1


## M ##  :  Multiple Volume Mode 

MPTool can scan several CDs or ZIPs

MPTool will ask you to insert a volume and press 'y' to list it.
When you have no more volumes to list, press 'n' and MPTool will print the
results.

NB: CLI>c:MPTool -M cd0: dh1:

    cd0: (the first argument) is affected by the M option
    dh1: will be listed once


                            @{" Back To The Options " link Options}  


@endnode
@node Optionsn


## n ##


It scans the given drawers and selects TAGged MP3 files, sorts them by
songname and displays the list ( -nR for working on subdrawers)

