@node MP3TAG


 6. The definition of a MP3-TAG :

It's a 128 bytes file attached to the end of a classic MP3 file

TAG      :   3 bytes (header of the TAG)
songname :  30 bytes
artist   :  30 bytes
album    :  30 bytes
year     :   4 bytes
comment  :  30 bytes or 29 bytes if the songnumber is used :)
type     :   1 bytes (genre from $00 [Blues] to $72 [Folklore]) 
           ___
 
total    : 128 bytes

The genre is given by one of the following number
( you can ADD your own genre by editing the file c:MPTool.Genres
  that's why I use an external file for the genres )

CLI>c:MPTool -g

