@node Problems


 7. Problems with MPTool : Problem/Solution


 P: The genre list doesn't appear || the genre is not shown
 S: Have you the file MPTool.Genres in c: ? with the correct name ?

 P: Some files are listed but are not MP3 files
 S: you have selected the D option and your file contains a pseudo MP3 header
    => you are not lucky and should not use the D option in that drawer

 P: Some files are NOT listed but I'm sure they are MP3 files
 S: Have you activated the Deep Scan Mode (D) ??
    If it's the case, please send me the first 10 KB of your file.

 P: When creating/editing a TAG, some strange things happen
 S: Delete them :) and don't press several keys at once.

 P: I wanted to cut a wave header / a TAG and nothing happens
 S: Check the file protection bits (RWED) to see if the file is not protected

 P: How do I create a text file ?
 S: Use the dos redirection : '>'  to create a new file
                              '>>' to add text to an exisiting one
    example :

    c:MPTool -L dh1: >ram:mylist.txt

    [the file mylist.txt will contain the list and nothing will be printed on
     the screen]

 P: It's not quite fast
 S: None, it has never been faster !

 P: It's on Amiga
 S: Amiga or die.


